George J. JUNKER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11309. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 4, 1946. Russell E. Parsons, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Charles H. Carr, U. S. Atty., and Ralph Lazarus, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los An-geles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and BONE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of the appellant, and of counsel for the respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this Court in this, cause issue forthwith. ■
